cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CVPR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category as the paper deals with visual odometry, which is a core problem in computer vision. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as visual odometry is an important component in robotics for navigation and localization. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper leverages deep learning techniques for estimating single-view depths and two-view optical flows. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper uses deep learning for improving the performance of visual odometry. 
5. cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another possible category as the paper presents a new approach for visual odometry which could be of interest to the computer vision community.
